    <releaseNotes>
### Added
- Add concurrent tasks
- Add more links to mod and modpack descriptions
- Add news reader in the launcher
- Add on-disk mod metadata information
- Implement mod updater
- Preliminary work for modpack updates
- Qt 6 support
- [Linux] Add Performance settings (MangoHud, GameMode and PRIME)
- [Linux] Add more metadata to Nix package
- [macOS] Implement updater using Sparkle
- [OpenBSD] Readd support for OpenBSD

### Changed
- Allow the cape to be changed without changing the skin
- Cleanup Java code
- Hide channel from version for tagged commits
- Improve handling of environment variables
- Improve resolving of JARs
- Improve the account selection window
- Improve UX in the mod downloader
- Improvements for Modrinth/CurseForge modpacks
- Improvements around APIs page
- Improvements to Windows installer
- Make version labels in About dialog selectable
- Make FTB Classic layout the same as other platforms
- Refactor instance resources pages
- Refactor tests
- Replace old reference to launchermeta.mojang.com
- Reword CurseForge warning
- Separate launch and kill instance actions
- Update license information
- [Linux] Cleanup flake.nix
- [Linux] Rewrite polymc.6 in scdoc
- [macOS] Build on macOS 12 in CI

### Fixed
- Always scale mod icons to the right size
- Don't censor offline access token
- Don't create unnecessary folders when extracting ZIPs
- Fix broken output in mod list
- Fix contrast of placeholder text with dark theme
- Fix duplicate name in window title
- Fix hangs when aborting some tasks
- Fix missing instance version in status bar
- Fix permanent mod-loaders for some modpacks
- Fix "Play Offline" not working when auth servers are partially offline
- Fix sorting for Modrinth resources
- Fix Technic instances using Forge
- Fix translations
- Fix warnings reported by LGTM.com
- [Linux] Fix mods relying on libstdc++ on Nix
- [Linux] Use our fork of libnbtplusplus on Nix
- [macOS] Workaround Qt bug to fix menu bar separators

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/PolyMC/PolyMC/compare/1.3.2...1.4.0
</releaseNotes>
